│ stop({"edit_points": [[1572, 1572, "llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/BasicTTIImpl.h"]], "thoughts": "1. Understanding the Issue: The crash occurs in                     │
│ `getIntrinsicInstrCost` when handling `llvm.powi` intrinsic. The issue is that `I` (the `IntrinsicInst` pointer) is `nullptr`, but the code at line 1572          │
│ dereferences it without checking: `I->getParent()->getParent()->hasOptSize()`. This causes a segmentation fault.\n\n2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log: The backtrace shows │
│ the crash originates from `BasicTTIImpl.h` line 1572. The `VPWidenCallRecipe::computeCost` creates an `IntrinsicCostAttributes` without passing an                │
│ `IntrinsicInst` (it passes `nullptr`), leading to `ICA.getInst()` returning `nullptr`. The `powi` case assumes `I` is non-null.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis: The    │
│ `powi` intrinsic cost calculation uses `I->getParent()->getParent()->hasOptSize()` to determine optimization-for-size context. However, when called from VPlan    │
│ cost estimation, there may be no concrete instruction available (`I` is `nullptr`). The code must guard against null `I`. Similar issues may exist for other      │
│ intrinsics that use `I` without checking.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s): At line 1572, we need to check if `I` is not null before dereferencing. If `I` is null,   │
│ we should use a default or fallback behavior. Since `hasOptSize()` is used to decide whether to expand `powi`, we can assume `false` (i.e., not optimizing for    │
│ size) when `I` is null, or perhaps use the function's `hasOptSize` from the target machine? However, looking at the context, `ShouldOptForSize` is used only to   │
│ call `isBeneficialToExpandPowI`. If `I` is null, we can pass `false` as a conservative default.\n\nEdit line 1572 to:\n`bool ShouldOptForSize = I &&              │
│ I->getParent()->getParent()->hasOptSize();`\n\n5. Conclusion: The fix adds a null check before dereferencing `I`. This prevents the segfault and provides a       │
│ reasonable default (false) when the instruction context is unavailable. This should resolve the crash while preserving correct behavior when `I` is available."}) │
